92. illis creditur: the Greeks flatter so skilfully that they are thought to be sincere.

93. an melior: does the actor on the stage play a part better? Even the best actors are nothing remarkable in Greece (illic), for every Greek is constantly playing a part in his intercourse with other men; of this, vss. roo—108 give examples. The meretrix (Thais), the uxor, and the aneilla (Doris) are the common female characters in comedy.
